Description: Catalyzes the attachment of serine to tRNA(Ser). Is also able to aminoacylate tRNA(Sec) with serine, to form the misacylated tRNA L-seryl-tRNA(Sec), which will be further converted into selenocysteinyl-tRNA(Sec)

Name: fluoride efflux transporter CrcB
Description: Important for reducing fluoride concentration in the cell, thus reducing its toxicity

Name: translation initiation factor IF-1
Description: One of the essential components for the initiation of protein synthesis. Stabilizes the binding of IF-2 and IF-3 on the 30S subunit to which N-formylmethionyl-tRNA(fMet) subsequently binds. Helps modulate mRNA selection, yielding the 30S pre- initiation complex (PIC). Upon addition of the 50S ribosomal subunit IF-1, IF-2 and IF-3 are released leaving the mature 70S translation initation complex

Name: NUDIX hydrolase
Description: Belongs to the Nudix hydrolase family. NudJ subfamily

Name: NADH-quinone oxidoreductase subunit L
Description: Catalyzes the transfer of electrons from NADH to ubiquinone

Name: NADH-quinone oxidoreductase subunit NuoN
Description: NDH-1 shuttles electrons from NADH, via FMN and iron- sulfur (Fe-S) centers, to quinones in the respiratory chain. The immediate electron acceptor for the enzyme in this species is believed to be ubiquinone. Couples the redox reaction to proton translocation (for every two electrons transferred, four hydrogen ions are translocated across the cytoplasmic membrane), and thus conserves the redox energy in a proton gradient

Name: toxin
Description: Cytotoxic translational repressor of toxin-antitoxin stability system

Name: peptidylprolyl isomerase
Description: PPIases accelerate the folding of proteins. It catalyzes the cis-trans isomerization of proline imidic peptide bonds in oligopeptides

Name: UDP-2,3-diacylglucosamine diphosphatase
Description: Hydrolyzes the pyrophosphate bond of UDP-2,3- diacylglucosamine to yield 2,3-diacylglucosamine 1-phosphate (lipid X) and UMP by catalyzing the attack of water at the alpha-P atom. Involved in the biosynthesis of lipid A, a phosphorylated glycolipid that anchors the lipopolysaccharide to the outer membrane of the cell

Name: EmrA/EmrK family multidrug efflux transporter periplasmic adaptor subunit
product: EmrA/EmrK family multidrug efflux transporter periplasmic adaptor subunit
Description: With ErmA and TolC forms a multidrug efflux system

Name: Translocation and assembly module subunit TamB
product: Translocation and assembly module subunit TamB
Description: TamB, inner membrane protein subunit of TAM complex

Name: Pyruvate dehydrogenase E1 component
Description: component of the pyruvate dehydrogenase (PDH) complex, that catalyzes the overall conversion of pyruvate to acetyl-CoA and CO(2)

Name: pyruvate dehydrogenase (acetyl-transferring), homodimeric type
Description: Component of the pyruvate dehydrogenase (PDH) complex, that catalyzes the overall conversion of pyruvate to acetyl-CoA and CO(2)

Name: trigger factor
Description: Involved in protein export. Acts as a chaperone by maintaining the newly synthesized protein in an open conformation. Functions as a peptidyl-prolyl cis-trans isomerase

Name: copper homeostasis periplasmic binding protein CopC
product: copper homeostasis periplasmic binding protein CopC

Name: Fructose import ATP-binding protein FrcA

product: Multidrug/solvent efflux pump outer membrane protein MepC

Name: 6-aminohexanoate-dimer hydrolase
Description: COG1680 Beta-lactamase class C and other penicillin binding proteins

Name: MFS domain-containing protein
Description: COG0477 Permeases of the major facilitator superfamily

Name: Amidohydro-rel domain-containing protein
Description: metal-dependent hydrolase of the TIM-barrel fold

Name: TIGR03752 family integrating conjugative element protein
product: TIGR03752 family integrating conjugative element protein

Description: Belongs to the class-II aminoacyl-tRNA synthetase family. Phe-tRNA synthetase alpha subunit type 1 subfamily

Name: 50S ribosomal protein L20
Description: Binds directly to 23S ribosomal RNA and is necessary for the in vitro assembly process of the 50S ribosomal subunit. It is not involved in the protein synthesizing functions of that subunit

Name: 3-isopropylmalate dehydratase small subunit
Description: Catalyzes the isomerization between 2-isopropylmalate and 3-isopropylmalate, via the formation of 2-isopropylmaleate

Name: 3-isopropylmalate dehydratase large subunit
Description: Catalyzes the isomerization between 2-isopropylmalate and 3-isopropylmalate, via the formation of 2-isopropylmaleate

Name: glucarate dehydratase
Description: Belongs to the mandelate racemase muconate lactonizing enzyme family

Name: osmoprotectant NAGGN system M42 family peptidase
product: osmoprotectant NAGGN system M42 family peptidase

Name: LysR family transcriptional regulator
Description: Bacterial regulatory helix-turn-helix protein, lysR family

Name: lipid A biosynthesis lauroyl acyltransferase
Description: Catalyzes the transfer of laurate from lauroyl-acyl carrier protein (ACP) to Kdo(2)-lipid IV(A) to form Kdo(2)- (lauroyl)-lipid IV(A)

Name: cell division topological specificity factor MinE
product: cell division topological specificity factor MinE
Description: Prevents the cell division inhibition by proteins MinC and MinD at internal division sites while permitting inhibition at polar sites. This ensures cell division at the proper site by restricting the formation of a division septum at the midpoint of the long axis of the cell

Name: RNA polymerase factor sigma-70
Description: Belongs to the sigma-70 factor family. ECF subfamily

Name: 2,4-dienoyl-CoA reductase
Description: COG1028 Dehydrogenases with different specificities (related to short-chain alcohol dehydrogenases)

Name: Pyrimidine/purine nucleoside phosphorylase
Description: Catalyzes the phosphorolysis of diverse nucleosides, yielding D-ribose 1-phosphate and the respective free bases. Can use uridine, adenosine, guanosine, cytidine, thymidine, inosine and xanthosine as substrates. Also catalyzes the reverse reactions

Name: flagellar motor protein
Description: this protein with a related protein (a MotB homolog) forms the ion channels that couple flagellar rotation to proton sodium motive force across the membrane and forms the stator elements of the rotary flagellar machine

Name: flagellar basal body-associated protein FliL
Description: Controls the rotational direction of flagella during chemotaxis

Name: flagellar hook-basal body complex protein FliE
product: flagellar hook-basal body complex protein FliE
Description: Flagellar hook-basal body complex protein FliE

Name: flagellar hook-associated protein FlgK
Description: Belongs to the flagella basal body rod proteins family

Name: Flagellar P-ring protein
Description: Assembles around the rod to form the L-ring and probably protects the motor basal body from shearing forces during rotation

Name: bifunctional adenosylcobinamide kinase/adenosylcobinamide-phosphate guanylyltransferase
Description: Catalyzes ATP-dependent phosphorylation of adenosylcobinamide and addition of GMP to adenosylcobinamide phosphate

Name: cobyric acid synthase
Description: Catalyzes amidations at positions B, D, E, and G on adenosylcobyrinic A,C-diamide. NH(2) groups are provided by glutamine, and one molecule of ATP is hydrogenolyzed for each amidation

Name: cytochrome-c oxidase, cbb3-type subunit I
Description: Belongs to the heme-copper respiratory oxidase family

Name: cytochrome-c oxidase, cbb3-type subunit II
Description: COG2993 Cbb3-type cytochrome oxidase, cytochrome c subunit

Name: cytochrome-c oxidase, cbb3-type subunit II
Description: COG2993 Cbb3-type cytochrome oxidase, cytochrome c subunit

Name: CcoQ/FixQ family Cbb3-type cytochrome c oxidase assembly chaperone
product: CcoQ/FixQ family Cbb3-type cytochrome c oxidase assembly chaperone

Name: DNA polymerase III subunit gamma/tau
Description: DNA polymerase III is a complex, multichain enzyme responsible for most of the replicative synthesis in bacteria. This DNA polymerase also exhibits 3' to 5' exonuclease activity

Name: amino acid ABC transporter substrate-binding protein
product: amino acid ABC transporter substrate-binding protein
Description: Amino acid ABC transporter substrate-binding protein

Name: EamA family transporter

Description: Catalyzes the thermodynamically favored C-C bond cleavage of (2R,3S)-2-methylisocitrate to yield pyruvate and succinate

Name: SDR family oxidoreductase
Description: COG1028 Dehydrogenases with different specificities (related to short-chain alcohol dehydrogenases)

Name: VapC toxin family PIN domain ribonuclease
product: VapC toxin family PIN domain ribonuclease
Description: Toxic component of a toxin-antitoxin (TA) module. An RNase

Name: amidase
Description: Allows the formation of correctly charged Gln-tRNA(Gln) through the transamidation of misacylated Glu-tRNA(Gln) in organisms which lack glutaminyl-tRNA synthetase. The reaction takes place in the presence of glutamine and ATP through an activated gamma-phospho-Glu-tRNA(Gln)

Name: sugar ABC transporter ATP-binding protein
Description: Belongs to the ABC transporter superfamily

Name: sugar ABC transporter permease
Description: Binding-protein-dependent transport system inner membrane component

Name: sugar ABC transporter permease
Description: COG1175 ABC-type sugar transport systems, permease components

Name: Superoxide dismutase [Fe]
Description: Destroys radicals which are normally produced within the cells and which are toxic to biological systems

Name: LTXXQ domain protein
Description: P pilus assembly Cpx signaling pathway, periplasmic inhibitor zinc-resistance associated protein

Name: glycine cleavage system protein GcvH
Description: The glycine cleavage system catalyzes the degradation of glycine. The H protein shuttles the methylamine group of glycine from the P protein to the T protein

Name: tol-pal system protein YbgF
Description: Mediates coordination of peptidoglycan synthesis and outer membrane constriction during cell division

Name: chaperonin GroEL
Description: Prevents misfolding and promotes the refolding and proper assembly of unfolded polypeptides generated under stress conditions

Name: co-chaperone GroES
Description: Binds to Cpn60 in the presence of Mg-ATP and suppresses the ATPase activity of the latter

Name: 50S ribosomal protein L19
Description: This protein is located at the 30S-50S ribosomal subunit interface and may play a role in the structure and function of the aminoacyl-tRNA binding site

Name: tRNA (guanosine(37)-N1)-methyltransferase TrmD
Description: Belongs to the RNA methyltransferase TrmD family

Name: ribosome maturation factor RimM
Description: An accessory protein needed during the final step in the assembly of 30S ribosomal subunit, possibly for assembly of the head region. Probably interacts with S19. Essential for efficient processing of 16S rRNA. May be needed both before and after RbfA during the maturation of 16S rRNA. It has affinity for free ribosomal 30S subunits but not for 70S ribosomes

Name: 30S ribosomal protein S16
Description: Belongs to the bacterial ribosomal protein bS16 family

Name: signal recognition particle protein
Description: Involved in targeting and insertion of nascent membrane proteins into the cytoplasmic membrane. Binds to the hydrophobic signal sequence of the ribosome-nascent chain (RNC) as it emerges from the ribosomes. The SRP-RNC complex is then targeted to the cytoplasmic membrane where it interacts with the SRP receptor FtsY. Interaction with FtsY leads to the transfer of the RNC complex to the Sec translocase for insertion into the membrane, the hydrolysis of GTP by both Ffh and FtsY, and the dissociation of the SRP-FtsY complex into the individual components

Name: formate-dependent phosphoribosylglycinamide formyltransferase
Description: Involved in the de novo purine biosynthesis. Catalyzes the transfer of formate to 5-phospho-ribosyl-glycinamide (GAR), producing 5-phospho-ribosyl-N-formylglycinamide (FGAR). Formate is provided by PurU via hydrolysis of 10-formyl-tetrahydrofolate

Name: glutamine-hydrolyzing GMP synthase
Description: Catalyzes the synthesis of GMP from XMP

Name: Inosine-5'-monophosphate dehydrogenase
Description: Catalyzes the conversion of inosine 5'-phosphate (IMP) to xanthosine 5'-phosphate (XMP), the first committed and rate- limiting step in the de novo synthesis of guanine nucleotides, and therefore plays an important role in the regulation of cell growth

Name: outer membrane protein assembly factor BamB
product: outer membrane protein assembly factor BamB
Description: Part of the outer membrane protein assembly complex, which is involved in assembly and insertion of beta-barrel proteins into the outer membrane

Name: histidine--tRNA ligase
Description: Catalyzes a two-step reaction, first charging a histidine molecule by linking its carboxyl group to the alpha-phosphate of ATP, followed by transfer of the aminoacyl-adenylate to its tRNA

Name: type IV pilus biogenesis/stability protein PilW
product: type IV pilus biogenesis/stability protein PilW

Name: 23S rRNA (adenine(2503)-C(2))-methyltransferase RlmN
Description: Specifically methylates position 2 of adenine 2503 in 23S rRNA and position 2 of adenine 37 in tRNAs

Name: nucleoside-diphosphate kinase
Description: Major role in the synthesis of nucleoside triphosphates other than ATP. The ATP gamma phosphate is transferred to the NDP beta phosphate via a ping-pong mechanism, using a phosphorylated active-site intermediate

Name: protein translocase subunit SecD
Description: Part of the Sec protein translocase complex. Interacts with the SecYEG preprotein conducting channel. SecDF uses the proton motive force (PMF) to complete protein translocation after the ATP-dependent function of SecA

Name: tRNA guanosine(34) transglycosylase Tgt
Description: Catalyzes the base-exchange of a guanine (G) residue with the queuine precursor 7-aminomethyl-7-deazaguanine (PreQ1) at position 34 (anticodon wobble position) in tRNAs with GU(N) anticodons (tRNA-Asp, -Asn, -His and -Tyr). Catalysis occurs through a double-displacement mechanism. The nucleophile active site attacks the C1' of nucleotide 34 to detach the guanine base from the RNA, forming a covalent enzyme-RNA intermediate. The proton acceptor active site deprotonates the incoming PreQ1, allowing a nucleophilic attack on the C1' of the ribose to form the product. After dissociation, two additional enzymatic reactions on the tRNA convert PreQ1 to queuine (Q), resulting in the hypermodified nucleoside queuosine (7-(((4,5-cis-dihydroxy-2- cyclopenten-1-yl)amino)methyl)-7-deazaguanosine)

Name: nitric oxide reductase transcriptional regulator NorR
product: nitric oxide reductase transcriptional regulator NorR

Name: Obg family GTPase CgtA
Description: An essential GTPase which binds GTP, GDP and possibly (p)ppGpp with moderate affinity, with high nucleotide exchange rates and a fairly low GTP hydrolysis rate. Plays a role in control of the cell cycle, stress response, ribosome biogenesis and in those bacteria that undergo differentiation, in morphogenesis control

Name: 50S ribosomal protein L27
Description: Belongs to the bacterial ribosomal protein bL27 family

Name: 50S ribosomal protein L21
Description: This protein binds to 23S rRNA in the presence of protein L20

Name: protein-methionine-sulfoxide reductase catalytic subunit MsrP
Description: Part of the MsrPQ system that repairs oxidized periplasmic proteins containing methionine sulfoxide residues (Met-O), using respiratory chain electrons. Thus protects these proteins from oxidative-stress damage caused by reactive species of oxygen and chlorine generated by the host defense mechanisms. MsrPQ is essential for the maintenance of envelope integrity under bleach stress, rescuing a wide series of structurally unrelated periplasmic proteins from methionine oxidation. The catalytic subunit MsrP is non-stereospecific, being able to reduce both (R-) and (S-) diastereoisomers of methionine sulfoxide

Name: CDP-diacylglycerol--serine O-phosphatidyltransferase
Description: Belongs to the CDP-alcohol phosphatidyltransferase class-I family

Name: RNA polymerase-binding protein DksA
Description: Transcription factor that acts by binding directly to the RNA polymerase (RNAP). Required for negative regulation of rRNA expression and positive regulation of several amino acid biosynthesis promoters. Also required for regulation of fis expression

Name: polyribonucleotide nucleotidyltransferase
Description: Involved in mRNA degradation. Catalyzes the phosphorolysis of single-stranded polyribonucleotides processively in the 3'- to 5'-direction

Name: 30S ribosomal protein S15
Description: Forms an intersubunit bridge (bridge B4) with the 23S rRNA of the 50S subunit in the ribosome

Name: tRNA pseudouridine(55) synthase TruB
Description: Responsible for synthesis of pseudouridine from uracil- 55 in the psi GC loop of transfer RNAs

Name: 30S ribosome-binding factor RbfA
Description: One of several proteins that assist in the late maturation steps of the functional core of the 30S ribosomal subunit. Associates with free 30S ribosomal subunits (but not with 30S subunits that are part of 70S ribosomes or polysomes). Required for efficient processing of 16S rRNA. May interact with the 5'-terminal helix region of 16S rRNA

Name: translation initiation factor IF-2
Description: One of the essential components for the initiation of protein synthesis. Protects formylmethionyl-tRNA from spontaneous hydrolysis and promotes its binding to the 30S ribosomal subunits. Also involved in the hydrolysis of GTP during the formation of the 70S ribosomal complex

Name: transcription termination/antitermination protein NusA
Description: Participates in both transcription termination and antitermination

Name: ribosome maturation factor RimP
Description: Required for maturation of 30S ribosomal subunits

Name: triose-phosphate isomerase
Description: Involved in the gluconeogenesis. Catalyzes stereospecifically the conversion of dihydroxyacetone phosphate (DHAP) to D-glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate (G3P)

Name: nucleotide exchange factor GrpE
Description: Participates actively in the response to hyperosmotic and heat shock by preventing the aggregation of stress-denatured proteins, in association with DnaK and GrpE. It is the nucleotide exchange factor for DnaK and may function as a thermosensor. Unfolded proteins bind initially to DnaJ

Name: DNA repair protein RecN
Description: May be involved in recombinational repair of damaged DNA

Name: DNA topoisomerase (ATP-hydrolyzing)
Description: A type II topoisomerase that negatively supercoils closed circular double-stranded (ds) DNA in an ATP-dependent manner to modulate DNA topology and maintain chromosomes in an underwound state. Negative supercoiling favors strand separation, and DNA replication, transcription, recombination and repair, all of which involve strand separation. Also able to catalyze the interconversion of other topological isomers of dsDNA rings, including catenanes and knotted rings. Type II topoisomerases break and join 2 DNA strands simultaneously in an ATP-dependent manner

Name: Serine hydroxymethyltransferase 1
Description: Catalyzes the reversible interconversion of serine and glycine with tetrahydrofolate (THF) serving as the one-carbon carrier. This reaction serves as the major source of one-carbon groups required for the biosynthesis of purines, thymidylate, methionine, and other important biomolecules. Also exhibits THF- independent aldolase activity toward beta-hydroxyamino acids, producing glycine and aldehydes, via a retro-aldol mechanism

Name: ligand-gated channel
Description: Secretin and TonB N terminus short domain

Name: leucine--tRNA ligase
Description: due to the large number of codons that tRNA(Leu) recognizes, the leucyl-tRNA synthetase does not recognize the anticodon loop of the tRNA, but instead recognition is dependent on a conserved discriminator base A37 and a long arm

Name: serine-type D-Ala-D-Ala carboxypeptidase
Description: Belongs to the peptidase S11 family

Name: septal ring lytic transglycosylase RlpA family lipoprotein
product: septal ring lytic transglycosylase RlpA family lipoprotein
Description: Lytic transglycosylase with a strong preference for naked glycan strands that lack stem peptides

Name: penicillin-binding protein 2
Description: Catalyzes cross-linking of the peptidoglycan cell wall

Name: nicotinate-nucleotide adenylyltransferase
Description: Catalyzes the reversible adenylation of nicotinate mononucleotide (NaMN) to nicotinic acid adenine dinucleotide (NaAD)

Name: Gamma-glutamyl phosphate reductase
Description: Catalyzes the NADPH-dependent reduction of L-glutamate 5-phosphate into L-glutamate 5-semialdehyde and phosphate. The product spontaneously undergoes cyclization to form 1-pyrroline-5- carboxylate

Name: inorganic diphosphatase
Description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of inorganic pyrophosphate (PPi) forming two phosphate ions

Name: exodeoxyribonuclease VII small subunit
Description: Bidirectionally degrades single-stranded DNA into large acid-insoluble oligonucleotides, which are then degraded further into small acid-soluble oligonucleotides

Name: (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate synthase
Description: Belongs to the FPP GGPP synthase family

Name: 1-deoxy-D-xylulose-5-phosphate synthase
Description: Catalyzes the acyloin condensation reaction between C atoms 2 and 3 of pyruvate and glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate to yield 1-deoxy-D-xylulose-5-phosphate (DXP)

Name: transcriptional regulator NrdR
Description: Negatively regulates transcription of bacterial ribonucleotide reductase nrd genes and operons by binding to NrdR- boxes

Name: Bacterioferritin
Description: Iron-storage protein, whose ferroxidase center binds Fe(2 ) ions, oxidizes them by dioxygen to Fe(3 ), and participates in the subsequent Fe(3 ) oxide mineral core formation within the central cavity of the protein complex

Name: DNA-directed RNA polymerase subunit alpha
Description: DNA-dependent RNA polymerase catalyzes the transcription of DNA into RNA using the four ribonucleoside triphosphates as substrates

Name: 30S ribosomal protein S4
Description: One of the primary rRNA binding proteins, it binds directly to 16S rRNA where it nucleates assembly of the body of the 30S subunit

Name: 30S ribosomal protein S11
Description: Located on the platform of the 30S subunit, it bridges several disparate RNA helices of the 16S rRNA. Forms part of the Shine-Dalgarno cleft in the 70S ribosome

Name: 30S ribosomal protein S13
Description: Located at the top of the head of the 30S subunit, it contacts several helices of the 16S rRNA. In the 70S ribosome it contacts the 23S rRNA (bridge B1a) and protein L5 of the 50S subunit (bridge B1b), connecting the 2 subunits

Name: preprotein translocase subunit SecY
Description: The central subunit of the protein translocation channel SecYEG. Consists of two halves formed by TMs 1-5 and 6-10. These two domains form a lateral gate at the front which open onto the bilayer between TMs 2 and 7, and are clamped together by SecE at the back. The channel is closed by both a pore ring composed of hydrophobic SecY resides and a short helix (helix 2A) on the extracellular side of the membrane which forms a plug. The plug probably moves laterally to allow the channel to open. The ring and the pore may move independently

Name: 30S ribosomal protein S5
Description: Located at the back of the 30S subunit body where it stabilizes the conformation of the head with respect to the body

Name: 50S ribosomal protein L6
Description: This protein binds to the 23S rRNA, and is important in its secondary structure. It is located near the subunit interface in the base of the L7 L12 stalk, and near the tRNA binding site of the peptidyltransferase center

Name: 30S ribosomal protein S8
Description: One of the primary rRNA binding proteins, it binds directly to 16S rRNA central domain where it helps coordinate assembly of the platform of the 30S subunit

Name: 30S ribosomal protein S14
Description: Binds 16S rRNA, required for the assembly of 30S particles and may also be responsible for determining the conformation of the 16S rRNA at the A site

Name: 50S ribosomal protein L5
Description: This is 1 of the proteins that binds and probably mediates the attachment of the 5S RNA into the large ribosomal subunit, where it forms part of the central protuberance. In the 70S ribosome it contacts protein S13 of the 30S subunit (bridge B1b), connecting the 2 subunits

Name: 50S ribosomal protein L22
Description: The globular domain of the protein is located near the polypeptide exit tunnel on the outside of the subunit, while an extended beta-hairpin is found that lines the wall of the exit tunnel in the center of the 70S ribosome

Name: 50S ribosomal protein L23
Description: One of the early assembly proteins it binds 23S rRNA. One of the proteins that surrounds the polypeptide exit tunnel on the outside of the ribosome. Forms the main docking site for trigger factor binding to the ribosome

Name: 30S ribosomal protein S10
Description: Involved in the binding of tRNA to the ribosomes

Name: elongation factor Tu
Description: This protein promotes the GTP-dependent binding of aminoacyl-tRNA to the A-site of ribosomes during protein biosynthesis

Name: elongation factor G
Description: Catalyzes the GTP-dependent ribosomal translocation step during translation elongation. During this step, the ribosome changes from the pre-translocational (PRE) to the post- translocational (POST) state as the newly formed A-site-bound peptidyl-tRNA and P-site-bound deacylated tRNA move to the P and E sites, respectively. Catalyzes the coordinated movement of the two tRNA molecules, the mRNA and conformational changes in the ribosome

Name: 30S ribosomal protein S7
Description: One of the primary rRNA binding proteins, it binds directly to 16S rRNA where it nucleates assembly of the head domain of the 30S subunit. Is located at the subunit interface close to the decoding center, probably blocks exit of the E-site tRNA

Name: 30S ribosomal protein S12
Description: Interacts with and stabilizes bases of the 16S rRNA that are involved in tRNA selection in the A site and with the mRNA backbone. Located at the interface of the 30S and 50S subunits, it traverses the body of the 30S subunit contacting proteins on the other side and probably holding the rRNA structure together. The combined cluster of proteins S8, S12 and S17 appears to hold together the shoulder and platform of the 30S subunit

Name: DNA-directed RNA polymerase subunit beta'
Description: DNA-dependent RNA polymerase catalyzes the transcription of DNA into RNA using the four ribonucleoside triphosphates as substrates

Name: DNA-directed RNA polymerase subunit beta
Description: DNA-dependent RNA polymerase catalyzes the transcription of DNA into RNA using the four ribonucleoside triphosphates as substrates

Name: 50S ribosomal protein L7/L12
Description: Forms part of the ribosomal stalk which helps the ribosome interact with GTP-bound translation factors. Is thus essential for accurate translation

Name: 50S ribosomal protein L10
Description: Forms part of the ribosomal stalk, playing a central role in the interaction of the ribosome with GTP-bound translation factors

Name: 50S ribosomal protein L1
Description: Binds directly to 23S rRNA. The L1 stalk is quite mobile in the ribosome, and is involved in E site tRNA release

Name: 50S ribosomal protein L11
Description: Forms part of the ribosomal stalk which helps the ribosome interact with GTP-bound translation factors

Name: transcription termination/antitermination protein NusG
Description: Participates in transcription elongation, termination and antitermination

Name: preprotein translocase subunit SecE
Description: Essential subunit of the Sec protein translocation channel SecYEG. Clamps together the 2 halves of SecY. May contact the channel plug during translocation

Name: N-acetyl-gamma-glutamyl-phosphate reductase
Description: Catalyzes the NADPH-dependent reduction of N-acetyl-5- glutamyl phosphate to yield N-acetyl-L-glutamate 5-semialdehyde

Name: 4-hydroxythreonine-4-phosphate dehydrogenase PdxA
Description: Catalyzes the NAD(P)-dependent oxidation of 4- (phosphohydroxy)-L-threonine (HTP) into 2-amino-3-oxo-4- (phosphohydroxy)butyric acid which spontaneously decarboxylates to form 3-amino-2-oxopropyl phosphate (AHAP)

Name: 16S rRNA (adenine(1518)-N(6)/adenine(1519)-N(6))-dimethyltransferase RsmA
Description: Specifically dimethylates two adjacent adenosines (A1518 and A1519) in the loop of a conserved hairpin near the 3'-end of 16S rRNA in the 30S particle. May play a critical role in biogenesis of 30S subunits

Name: 30S ribosomal protein S21
Description: Belongs to the bacterial ribosomal protein bS21 family

Name: pyrroloquinoline quinone biosynthesis protein PqqB
Description: May be involved in the transport of PQQ or its precursor to the periplasm

Name: pyrroloquinoline quinone biosynthesis peptide chaperone PqqD
product: pyrroloquinoline quinone biosynthesis peptide chaperone PqqD

Name: transketolase

Name: DEAD/DEAH box helicase
Description: DEAD-box RNA helicase involved in ribosome assembly. Has RNA-dependent ATPase activity and unwinds double-stranded RNA

Name: pyrroline-5-carboxylate reductase
Description: Catalyzes the reduction of 1-pyrroline-5-carboxylate (PCA) to L-proline

Name: pantetheine-phosphate adenylyltransferase
Description: Reversibly transfers an adenylyl group from ATP to 4'- phosphopantetheine, yielding dephospho-CoA (dPCoA) and pyrophosphate

Name: phosphoglycerate dehydrogenase
Description: Belongs to the D-isomer specific 2-hydroxyacid dehydrogenase family

Name: transcription termination factor Rho
Description: Facilitates transcription termination by a mechanism that involves Rho binding to the nascent RNA, activation of Rho's RNA-dependent ATPase activity, and release of the mRNA from the DNA template

Name: 50S ribosomal protein L28
Description: Belongs to the bacterial ribosomal protein bL28 family

Name: dUTP diphosphatase
Description: This enzyme is involved in nucleotide metabolism it produces dUMP, the immediate precursor of thymidine nucleotides and it decreases the intracellular concentration of dUTP so that uracil cannot be incorporated into DNA

Name: bifunctional GTP diphosphokinase/guanosine-3',5'-bis pyrophosphate 3'-pyrophosphohydrolase
Description: In eubacteria ppGpp (guanosine 3'-diphosphate 5-' diphosphate) is a mediator of the stringent response that coordinates a variety of cellular activities in response to changes in nutritional abundance

Name: ABC transporter ATP-binding protein
Description: P-loop containing region of AAA domain

Name: type VI secretion system membrane subunit TssM
product: type VI secretion system membrane subunit TssM

Name: DotU family type VI secretion system protein
product: DotU family type VI secretion system protein
Description: Type VI secretion system protein DotU

Name: type VI secretion system baseplate subunit TssK
product: type VI secretion system baseplate subunit TssK

Name: type VI secretion system lipoprotein TssJ
product: type VI secretion system lipoprotein TssJ
Description: Type VI secretion lipoprotein, VasD, EvfM, TssJ, VC_A0113

Name: type VI secretion system protein TssA
